<paragraph blockId="105.[189,1399,314,411]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[480,585,314,340]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioica">
<emphasis box="[480,585,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">B. dioica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and both species can be found in the neighbouring countries of 
<collectingCountry box="[1328,1398,314,340]" name="Nepal" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[239,355,350,376]" name="Myanmar" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
. They are similar vegetatively but 
<taxonomicName box="[761,878,349,375]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubella">
<emphasis box="[761,878,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">B. rubella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has much smaller flowers that are similar in size to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": de Candolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[373,518,384,410]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovatifolia">
<emphasis box="[373,518,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">B. ovatifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
